Found some notes here: https://github.com/openzipkin/openzipkin.github.io/wiki/2019-04-17-UX-workshop-and-Lens-GA-planning-at-LINE-Fukuoka

I added a custom error parser to figure out what the exception was about..

```
+      .errorParser(new ErrorParser() {
+                     @Override protected void error(Throwable error, Object span) {
+                       String className = error.getClass().getSimpleName();
+                       String message = error.getMessage();
+                       if (message == null) {
+                         message = className + "(" + message + ")";
+                       } else {
+                         message = className;
+                       }
+                       StringWriter sw = new StringWriter();
+                       PrintWriter pw = new PrintWriter(sw);
+                       error.printStackTrace(pw);
+                       tag(span, "error", message);
+                       tag(span, "error.stack", sw.toString());
+                     }
+                   }
+      )
```

Looks like were hitting an exception at the storage layer, just not a remote one. I'll patch the code to also consider load errors one enqueue:

